Class CrimeDataLoadingFragment.KodUtvaruLoadingTaskHandler

    protected class CrimeDataLoadingFragment.KodUtvaruLoadingTaskHandler
extends java.lang.Object
implements AsyncTaskHandler<UtvarKodANazev>
    KodUtvaruLoadingTaskHandler is the helper class to wrap and handle the instance of GetKodAktualnihoUtvaruAsyncTask for the CrimeDataLoadingFragment fragment.

    This class is an AsyncTaskHandler, which means it listens for the lifecycle callbacks of the wrapped GetKodAktualnihoUtvaruAsyncTask and calls the callback methods in this fragment if appropriate.

    There only is at most one instance of this class for the CrimeDataLoadingFragment at any point.

    For each department loading task request there is a new instance of this class to wrap it.

        public void onPostExecute(UtvarKodANazev result)
        Called when the wrapped task calls its AsyncTask.onPostExecute.

        The owning fragment is notified.

        • If there was an error, the owning fragment's CrimeDataLoadingFragment.onKodUtvaruLoadingError is called.
        • If an empty result was retrieved, the owning fragment's CrimeDataLoadingFragment.onKodUtvaruEmptyDataLoaded is called.
        • If the crime data was successfuly loaded, the owning fragment's CrimeDataLoadingFragment.onKodUtvaruLoaded is called.
